=== Year 1 === At the end of Year 1, you can contribute $17,000 to the 401(k).
Since you have not exhausted all your tax-advantaged space, you can move part of your emergency fund in the taxable account to the Roth IRA by making a $7,500 deposit into it, leaving behind $8,500 in the taxable account. You still have $16,000 in your emergency fund, only now it's split between two different accounts.
This leaves you with:
