=== Year 2 === For Year 2, now you can contribute $24,500 to the 401(k) but that is the most you can do. You can shift another $7,500 from your taxable account into the Roth IRA, allocated toward the emergency fund. You still have $1,000 left over in the taxable account. Your overall emergency fund is still at $16,000, only you have $1,000 in taxable and $15,000 in the Roth IRA.
