'''Overall'''
{| class="wikitable" border="1" |- ! width="150"|Category ! width="150"|Balance |- | Retirement |align="center"| $56,500 |- | Emergency Fund |align="center"| $16,000 |- | '''TOTAL''' |align="center"| '''$72,500''' |- |}
=== Year 3 === In Year 3, you now can contribute a total of $32,000 to max out your tax-advantaged space, with $24,500 to 401(k) and $7,000 to Roth IRA. There is no longer any more room in the Roth IRA to shift emergency fund money.
At the end of the year, the accounts look like this:
'''Taxable Account''' {| class="wikitable" border="1" |- ! width="150"| Fund ! width="150"|Balance ! width="150"|Allocated Toward ! width="200"| Notes |- | Money Market |align="center"| $1,000 | Emergency Fund | Beginning Balance |- | '''Money Market TOTAL''' | align="center"| '''$1,000''' | Emergency Fund | &nbsp; |- | colspan="4" | &nbsp; |- | '''ACCOUNT TOTAL''' | align="center"| '''$1,000''' | colspan="2" | &nbsp; |- |}
'''Roth IRA''' {| class="wikitable" border="1" |- ! width="150"|Fund ! width="150"|Balance ! width="150"|Allocated Toward ! width="200"|Notes |- | Stocks |align="center"| &nbsp;&nbsp;$3,000 | Retirement | Starting balance |- | Stocks |align="center"| + $7,500 | Retirement | Annual IRA Contribution |- | '''Stocks TOTAL''' |align="center"| '''$10,500''' | colspan="2" |Retirement |- | colspan="4" | &nbsp; |- | Money Market |align="center"| $15,000 | Emergency Fund | Beginning balance |- | '''Money Market TOTAL''' |align="center"| '''$15,000''' | Emergency Fund | &nbsp; |- | colspan="4"| &nbsp; |- | '''ACCOUNT TOTAL''' |align="center"| '''$25,500''' | colspan="2" | &nbsp; |}
